description: Most of the miscellany of texts in CCCC MS 331, written in the fifteenth century, are concerned with the Eucharist. The main text is Baldwin of Ford OCist (d. 1190), De sacramento altaris which is also contained in CCCC MS 200, a manuscript written contemporary with its author. Others include Lanfranc OSB (d. 1089), De corpore et sanguine Domini, Paschasius Radbertus (c. 785-c. 860), De corpore et sanguine Domini, and John Tissington OFM (d. c. 1395), Confessio de sacramento altaris. The manuscript also contains sermons and letters mostly relating to the same subject.
